cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the feasibility and potential benefits of using cellular networks for TV distribution, which falls under the category of networked systems and technologies. Therefore, cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves modeling and analysis of TV viewing patterns and cellular technologies, which could fall under cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.IT (information theory). The paper also discusses the spectrum efficiency of the proposed system, which could fall under cs.CR (cryptography and security) and cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
